{"key":"post-6076702","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6076702</id>\n<content>Use one to one and a half inches of water. Turn the stove on high. Leave the weight off for the first five minutes of steam escape.  After five minutes put the weight on.  When pressure is reached, the weight will rattle to let the excess steam off.  At this point, reduce the stove to the minimum setting that will maintain 15PSI without excessive rattling of the weight. Begin time when pressure is reached.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6077246</next>\n<prev>6076683</prev>\n<first>6076651</first>\n<last>6077246</last>\n<when>1158647423</when>\n<utime>09/19/06 09:30 AM</utime>\n</post>"}